      {
        "content": "Social media platforms routinely harvest vast amounts of personal data, often without clear user consent, compromising individual privacy. This pervasive data collection enables surveillance capitalism, where users become products sold to advertisers, infringing on their autonomy and security. The lack of transparency in data handling practices increases the risk of breaches and misuse, potentially leading to identity theft and other privacy violations. Reform is essential to ensure robust privacy protections, including stricter regulations, user control over data, and transparent policies. Upholding privacy is crucial for maintaining trust and safeguarding fundamental human rights in the digital age.",
